LS16 Hyne Tumbarumba Data for Stan

For each test log:

  • Stress Wave Velocity
  • SED, LED, Length
  • Sweep
  • Principal
  • Orthogonal
  • % heartwood
  • Large end
  • Small end
  • Taper and waist from a quadratic fit to polygonal area (not sure what that waist parameter is)
  • Whorl-i-ness
library(RODBC)
library(RODBC)
ch = odbcConnect('Hyne',uid='sa',pwd="password12")
sql = "select 
  p.SWILogNumber as SWILogNumber, 
  t.SWV as [SWV.hitman], 
  t.LED as [LED.yard], 
  t.SED as [SED.yard], 
  t.length as Length,   
  t.weight [log.weight],
  p.volume,
  p.m_sweep1 as SweepPrincipal,
  p.m_sweep2 as SweepOrthogonal,
  p.m_taper as Taper,
  p.m_waist as Waist,
  p.m_whorliness as Whorliness,
  (rL*rL*1e6)/(t.LED*t.LED/4)*100 as LEheartPercent, 
  (rS*rS*1e6)/(t.SED*t.SED/4)*100 as SEheartPercent,
  3.141592654*4.9/3*(rL*rL+rS*rL+rS*rS) as [volume.heart],
  q.nboards*4.9*0.0905*0.0349/p.volume as vfracRecovered,
  q.abc_avg as ABC           
from 
  (select * 
     from logs 
   where SWILogNumber is not null 
   and DateAndTime>'2014-08-31 00:00:00') p
left join (select * 
             from logs 
             where SWILogNumber is not null 
             and DateAndTime<'2014-08-31 00:00:00') s 
  on s.SWILogNumber=p.SWILogNumber
left join yardTrimmed t 
  on p.SWILogNumber=t.SWILogNumber 
left join yardUntrimmed u 
  on p.SWILogNumber=u.SWILogNumber 
left join (select 
             l.SWILogNumber, 
             l.heartwoodDiameter_mm/2000 rL, 
             s.heartwoodDiameter_mm/2000 rS 
           from 
             logends l, 
             logends s 
           where 
             s.SWILogNumber=l.SWILogNumber 
             and s.logEnd='S' 
             and l.logEnd='L') h 
  on h.SWILogNumber=p.SWILogNumber
left join tmp_logquality q on q.SWILogNumber=p.SWILogNumber
order by p.SWILogNumber"
L = sqlQuery(ch,sql)
write.csv(L, row.names=FALSE, quote=FALSE, file="/home/harrinjj/Desktop/Dropbox/4stan/hyne-logs.csv")

Inner ten ring area not available for hyne logs. If needed, can be derived from log end images.

All trial logs were trimmed to 4.9m, some from the small end some from the large. The SWV is that measured using Hitman on the trimmed log.

Log shape data every 6 along the length (scanner resolution)

  • Diameter (polygonal)
  • Eliptical shape
  • Major diameter
  • Minor diameter
  • Orientation of major diameter (degrees) relative to a fixed coordinate system
  • Ovality
  • Area (polygonal)

See hyne-xsectns.csv in dropbox folder. Generated by logmetrics.Rmd and USNR/reprocess.py. The shape data used is from the ELI scanner, whereas the summary data above comes from the ROY scanner. There will be small differences.

For each piece of lumber sawn from the log

  • log id
  • Length
  • Width
  • Thickness
  • Warp (signed twist, crook, bow)
  • MOE
  • Density
  • Visual Grade
  • Whether inner or outer
  • MC at time warp data obtained
B = sqlQuery(ch, "
             select
                m.flitchId,
                SWILogNumber,
                m.swv [swv.hitman_m/s], 
                m.pith, 
                m.wane,
                m.inCant,
                m.bow bow_mm,
                m.crook crook_mm,
                m.twist twist_mm,
                m.mc [MC%],
                X_Dens [density_kg/m3],
                O_Width/10 as width_mm,
                O_Thick/10 as thick_mm,
                O_Len as length_mm,  
                xc, yc
             from (
                select 
                  flitchId, 
                  max(pith) pith, 
                  max(wane) wane, 
                  avg(swv) swv, 
                  avg(bow) bow, 
                  avg(crook) crook, 
                  avg(twist) twist,
                  max(inCant) inCant,
                  avg(mc) mc
                from manualMeas group by flitchId
             ) m 
             left join CHHBoards c on c.flitchId=m.flitchId
             left join HyneDryBoards h on h.flitchId=m.flitchId
             left join ecoustic g on m.flitchId=g.flitchId
             left join (
                select 
                  flitchId, 
                  max(SWILogNumber) SWILogNumber 
                from 
                  boardEndImages i, barcode_image bi, boardEndBarcodes b 
                where flitchId is not null and i.id=bi.imageId and bi.barcodeId=b.id group by flitchId
             ) f on f.flitchId=m.flitchId
             left join (
                select FlitchID, avg(boardCentroidX_mm) xc, avg(boardCentroidY_mm) yc
                from boardEndBarcodes b, boardEndImages i, barcode_image bi
                where b.id=bi.barcodeId and i.id=bi.imageId
                group by FlitchID
             ) xy on xy.FlitchID=m.flitchId
             ")
B$moe_GPa = B$swv.hitman^2*B$density/1e9
B$R_mm = sqrt(B$xc^2 + B$yc^2)
B$kappa.z = 8*B$crook / (4.9)^2
B$kappa.y = 8*B$bow / (4.9)^2
B$abc = sqrt(B$kappa.z^2 + B$kappa.y^2)
write.csv(B, row.names=FALSE, quote=FALSE, file="/home/harrinjj/Desktop/Dropbox/4stan/hyne-boards.csv")

The board data is from the manual measurements or the from the mill data collected at CHH Tumut.

Warp was assessed only for nominal 90x40 boards (some of which had varying amounts of wane).

Visual grade was never assessed. Ive not labelled boards inner or outer, but have included distance from the pith (R, mm). Distance from the pith was only assessed on large end, and since all the logs in the study are butt logs, the pith wander near the large end characteristic of such logs probably limits the representativeness of these distances.

Moisture content was measured on only a few boards using a Wagner resistance meter.
